  <reg:title>Provincial Court Practice Directions Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[includes amendments up to B.C. Reg. 99/2018, May 18, 2018]</reg:amsincluded>
  <reg:regpitid>188_98_pit</reg:regpitid>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e32" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Application</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>This regulation applies in respect of proceedings before the Provincial Court under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/11025_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Family Law Act</in:doc></bcl:link> in which an order for guardianship, parenting arrangements, contact or support is sought or in which variation of such an order is sought.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 379/2012.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e50">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Directions to attend parenting programs</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:subsection id="d2e58">
        <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>The Chief Judge of the Provincial Court may give directions requiring parties in proceedings to attend parenting programs operated by the Ministry of Attorney General.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d2e67">
        <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>The Chief Judge may designate registries of the Provincial Court to which a direction under subsection (1) applies.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Regs. 27/2013, Sch. 2, s. 9; 99/2018, Sch. 2, s. 14.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96379_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Provincial Court Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 379,  section 11 (1) (d)]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
